The article is about the proclamation made by President Barack Obama in June 2009, declaring June as National Caribbean-American Heritage Month. The proclamation honors the cultural, linguistic, ethnic, and social diversity of Caribbean Americans and recognizes their contributions to the nation's culture and history. It highlights the traditions and vibrant culture brought by Caribbean Americans, as well as their determination, devotion to community, and patriotism. The proclamation also emphasizes the importance of the relationship between the United States and Caribbean nations, urging all Americans to learn more about the history and culture of Caribbean Americans.